-- Argentina Finance Chief Lorenzino Confident of Reaching Bond-Swap Goal
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-06-16T10:37:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/argentina-finance-chief-lorenzino-confident-of-reaching-bond-swap-goal.html

          
          
             Argentina’s government is confident
that its offer to swap defaulted bonds will be accepted by at
least 60 percent of bondholders, Argentine Finance Secretary
Hernan Lorenzino said at a press conference in Milan.  
 As of June 11, creditors tendered about 56 percent of the
outstanding bonds, the governemnt said this week.  
 The swap offer won’t be extended beyond a June 22 deadline,
Lorenzino said today.   
